<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900515-0131</DOCNO><DOCID>900515-0131.</DOCID><HL>   Moody's Downgrades   Debt of McDonnell</HL><DATE>05/15/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C23</SO><CO>   MD</CO><IN>BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)</IN><LP>   ST. LOUIS -- Moody's Investors Service Inc., citing thedeteriorating outlook for defense contractors, lowered itsratings on about $3.4 billion of McDonnell Douglas Corp.'ssenior and subordinated debt.   Moody's downgraded McDonnell Douglas's senior debt andshelf registration to Baa-1 from single-A-3, and subordinateddebt to Baa-2 from Baa-1.</LP><TEXT>   The rating concern said its action also was based onMcDonnell Douglas's &quot;continuing operating difficulties at itscommercial aircraft operations.&quot;   A McDonnell Douglas spokesman said the company wasnotified by Moody's several weeks ago that it might downgradethe debt. &quot;Everybody knows we're experiencing financialdifficulties, particularly in our transport-aircraftbusiness, where we had an operating loss of $84 million inthe first quarter,&quot; the spokesman said. &quot;But that's also anarea where we think there's tremendous potential.&quot;   In New York Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday,McDonnell Douglas shares closed at $47.875, down $1.</TEXT></DOC>